== Chemical properties ==

Following is a table listing the one-letter symbols, the three-letter symbols, and the chemical properties of the side chains of the standard amino acids. The masses listed are based on weighted averages of the elemental isotopes at their natural abundances. Forming a peptide bond results in elimination of a molecule of water. Therefore, the protein&#x27;s mass is equal to the mass of amino acids the protein is composed of minus 18.01524 Da per peptide bond.

