<doc id="427505" wikidata="Q5154412" url="?curid=427505" title="Communist Party of Kyrgyzstan">
<text>The Communist Party of Kyrgyzstan () is a communist party in Kyrgyzstan. It was founded on 21 August 1999, following a split in the Party of Communists of Kyrgyzstan.

KPK did not participate in the 2000 parliamentary elections. It publishes &quot;Kommunisty Kyrgyzstana&quot;.

The party is affiliated to the Communist Party of the Soviet Union of Oleg Shenin.

